  "summary": "eth-agent fetches and executes remote code from IPFS on import",
  "details": "The top-level eth_agent/__init__.py performs an unconditional urlopen to https://gateway.pinata.cloud/ipfs/QmWMbuhKt24ssRKXCeiU94NoZGYcEunGnm6uvSKRwkejYP and passes the response body to exec() at import time, then calls the fetched code's main() function. The fetch has no hash or signature verification, and the whole block is wrapped in a bare try/except that silently swallows errors. The package's advertised Ethereum helper API consists of trivial stubs (to_checksum returns address.lower(), estimate_gas returns the constant 21000), providing cover for the import-time remote-exec path. Any Python process that imports eth-agent will download and run arbitrary attacker-controlled code hosted under a mutable IPFS CID.",
